1.title: Face Your Fears
1.plot: In the season premiere of Face Off, twelve of your favorite artists return to the competition with a twist: this time they're battling.

2.title: Moonlight Monsters
2.plot: In the first elimination challenge this season, the artists have to create fun and lighthearted monsters inspired by real life day jobs.

3.title: Aztec Aliens
3.plot: The artists have to create ancient aliens that could have been the inspiration for Aztec Gods.

4.title: Haunted Hotel
4.plot: In this elimination challenge, the artists have to create the quirky and ghostly staff of a haunted hotel.

5.title: Death Dealers
5.plot: Fortune favors the bold this week, as the artists and their battle partners create makeups based on actual tarot card readings.

6.title: Divine Dryads
6.plot: The artists battle it out as they create dryad protectors of real life forests in this week's elimination challenge, with two more artists heading home.

7.title: Maritime Monsters
7.plot: The competition tightens as the six remaining artists create original sea monsters in this week's battles, with the help of an industry expert in next week's elimination challenge on the line.

8.title: Immortals Interrupted
8.plot: It's the semifinals and the artists engage in an all out battle royale, as they create vampires based on real life bats with just three finale spots on the line.

9.title: Through the Looking Glass, Part 1
9.plot: It's part one of the finale, as the finalists learn that they will be creating characters for an original short film based on the book, "Through the Looking Glass and What Alice Found There."

10.title: Through the Looking Glass, Part 2
10.plot: It's part two of the Face Off: Battle Royale finale, as the artists and their teams create their short film, and one is crowned champion.

1.title: Welcome to the Jungle
1.plot: The series premiere introduces twelve of the brightest up-and-coming special-effects make-up artists, who meet in Los Angeles for their first elimination challenge. Their task is to imagine an entirely new species - a human/animal hybrid - based on one of three exotic animals that are brought into their workspace lab.

2.title: Naked Ambition
2.plot: In the second episode of Face Off, the artists must apply original full body make-up to nude subjects in the vein of Demi Moore's "Birthday Suit" cover for Vanity Fair.

3.title: Out of This World
3.plot: For the spotlight challenge, the artists visit the famous Star Trek television series filming location, Vasquez Rocks, in Southern California. While there, they are given details on their next challenge from legendary FX artist Michael Westmore, best known for his make-up work in various Star Trek productions.

4.title: Bad to the Bone
4.plot: The artists pay a visit to the backlot of Universal Studios and the iconic Psycho House, where they meet Sean Cunningham, director and producer of the original Friday the 13th.

5.title: Switched and Hitched
5.plot: The contestants are divided into teams of two and challenged to transform a "bride" into a "groom" and a "groom" into a "bride".

6.title: The Dancing Dead
6.plot: For this week's spotlight challenge, the contestants must craft an original zombie. Their design must not only be creative, it must be functional and able to withstand the rigors of performing a choreographed dance routine.

7.title: Family Plot
7.plot: The families of the five remaining competitors are stationed in a local Los Angeles wig shop in order to play a part in this week's spotlight challenge.

8.title: Twisted Tales
8.plot: In the final spotlight challenge, the remaining three contestants are assigned a classic fairy tale such as Hansel and Gretel, Little Red Riding Hood and the Three Little Pigs.

1.title: Return to Oz
1.plot: It's the men versus the women in a challenge to recreate four iconic characters from the classic book, "The Wonderful Wizard of Oz."

2.title: Water World
2.plot: Contestants arrive at the Long Beach Aquarium of the Pacific and are asked to create sea creature makeups that can stay applied underwater.

3.title: Rock Your Body
3.plot: Contestants are asked to create art worthy of hip-hop star Asher Roth's album cover, but are surprised to find out they'll be body-painting nude models. GUEST JUDGE: Asher Roth

4.title: Night Terrors
4.plot: Contestants receive a startling message in the middle of the night and must face their fears to create unique horror villains. GUEST JUDGE: Tom Savini

5.title: Dangerous Beauty
5.plot: Based on dangerous plants and animals, contestants must create a creature that is both beautiful and deadly. GUEST JUDGES: Vivica A. Fox and Being Human's Sam Huntington

6.title: Triple Threat
6.plot: The contestants work in teams to complete old age make-ups on twins, but soon discover that their models are really triplets, and so the teams must devise new strategies to finish in time.

7.title: Alien Interpreters
7.plot: The contestants work with a special surprise client in order to create an original alien creature.

8.title: Burtonesque
8.plot: Contestants are challenged to create a whimsical character that is worthy of appearing in a Tim Burton film.

9.title: Dinoplasty
9.plot: Contestants visit the Los Angeles Natural History Museum where they are tasked with creating a human-dinosaur hybrid.

10.title: The Ultimate Spotlight Challenge
10.plot: The remaining contestants are shocked to learn their final creations will be unveiled as part of a dance routine in front of a large audience. One competitor is named the series winner.

1.title: A Force to Be Reckoned With
1.plot: Hollywood star Sean Astin welcomes the cast to season three, and the artists create original aliens for the classic Star Wars cantina scene.

2.title: Pirate Treasure
2.plot: The artists create original pirate makeups, and in a Face Off first, compete to win their very own pirate's booty - $5,000 cash.

3.title: Year of the Dragon
3.plot: The artists team up to create their own version of a traditional Chinese New Year dragon that will have to withstand the twists and turns of a spectacular acrobatic dance routine.

4.title: Alice in Zombieland
4.plot: The artists are asked to create original zombie makeups based on classic characters from Alice's Adventures in Wonderland.

5.title: Supermobile
5.plot: The artists team up in pairs and use amazing vehicles to inspire original superheroes and sidekicks. Writer and Director Kevin Smith guest judges.

6.title: Dishonorable Proportions
6.plot: The artists are asked to create wildly distorted and exaggerated characters based on the new video game, Dishonored.

7.title: Monster Twist
7.plot: The artists are surprised to find out that they'll be creating original movie monsters based on children's sketches, and a surprise twist changes the course of the entire season.

8.title: Who's the New Who?
8.plot: The artists create original makeups inspired by the 50th anniversary of the Dr. Seuss classic, Sleep Book. Iconic producer Brian Grazer guest judges.

9.title: Junkyard Cyborg
9.plot: The artists must source parts from a junkyard to create original cyborg makeups. Award-winning producer Gale Anne Hurd guest judges.

10.title: Scene of the Crime
10.plot: The artists create original makeups based on the world of the hit NBC fantasy crime drama, Grimm. Grimm star Silas Weir Mitchell makes a special guest appearance.

11.title: Immortal Enemies
11.plot: In their final Spotlight Challenge of the season, the three remaining artists are asked to create two Halloween-themed characters that must then perform in a spectacular choreographed stunt.

12.title: Live Reunion
12.plot: The crowning finale event of the season three finale of the hit reality competition series Face Off, broadcast live from Los Angeles, CA on Halloween night 2012 at 10 p.m. ET.

1.title: Make It Reign
1.plot: In their first Spotlight Challenge, the 14 artists create stunning fantasy goblin kings and are judged by Hollywood royalty, iconic actor John Rhys-Davies.

2.title: Heroic Proportions
2.plot: The artists create original superheroes for the season's first individual Spotlight Challenge and compete for the chance to have their design featured in a DC Comics book.

3.title: When Hell Freezes Over
3.plot: The artists tackle a sinister demon challenge and are later faced with an unexpected twist.

4.title: Eye Candy
4.plot: The artists create confection-inspired creatures incorporating real candy found throughout the sweetly transformed lab.

5.title: Two Heads Are Better Than One
5.plot: The artists team up to tackle larger-than-life giant characters based on the ancient fable, Jack the Giant Killer. Guest judge: Writer, producer and director, Bryan Singer.

6.title: Bugging Out
6.plot: The artists choose abstract, microscopic images and are surprised to find out they are the inspiration for a creepy-crawly bug-themed Spotlight Challenge.\

7.title: Howl at the Moon
7.plot: The artists create a horde of zombies, then head out into the moonlit night and team up to create planet-inspired alien werewolves.

8.title: It's Better in the Dark
8.plot: The seven remaining artists create never-before-seen creatures that glow in the dark, and are faced with a high-stakes twist.

9.title: Mummy Mayhem
9.plot: The remaining artists create Egyptian God mummies inspired by the Evil Dead franchise.

10.title: Alien Apocalypse
10.plot: The artists are surprised with a trip to Toronto where they visit the set of the epic new Syfy series, Defiance to inspire original alien creations.

11.title: Living the Dream
11.plot: Three finalists face the incredibly difficult task of creating waterproof makeups for the spectacular show, Le Reve: The Dream at the Wynn Hotel in Las Vegas.

1.title: Going for Gold
1.plot: In their first Spotlight Challenge, eight newcomers take on eight former contestants as each team creates a series of hyper-stylized fantasy characters. Hosted by McKenzie Westmore.

2.title: Future Frankenstein
2.plot: The artists create their own futuristic Frankenstein monsters and brides.

3.title: Gettin' Goosed
3.plot: The artists team up to create whimsical characters for modern times inspired by a classic Mother Goose nursery rhyme. Two artists are eliminated.

4.title: Subterranean Terror
4.plot: The artists explore abandoned tunnels in search of clues that inspire humanoid underground monsters.

5.title: Mother Earth Goddess
5.plot: The artists incorporate elements from both an arboretum and their own mothers in a challenge that requires them to creature Mother Nature goddesses.

6.title: Trick or Treat
6.plot: Reimagining classic Halloween characters gets tricky when the artists are asked to incorporate a "gag" element in their designs.

7.title: Living Art
7.plot: The artists create characters that could live within iconic art movements, including surrealism, cubism, and expressionism.

8.title: Cosmic Circus
8.plot: Team dynamics and a tough challenge take their toll on the artists who are faced with creating dark and sexy alien circus characters for an out-of-this-world performance.

9.title: Mortal Sins
9.plot: The artists arrive at a beautiful gothic church and learn that they must each create a character that embodies one of the seven deadly sins.

10.title: The Laughing Dead
10.plot: The artists arrive at the famous Laugh Factory comedy club in Hollywood and are tasked with creating an original ghost character that is both funny and scary.

11.title: Dark Magic
11.plot: The artists arrive at beautiful Kenneth Hahn Park and are asked to choose magical Norse runes to inspire a dark elf warrior character.

12.title: Flights of Fantasy
12.plot: Pressure is at an all-time high as the remaining four veteran artists create original human-bird hybrids in their final Spotlight Challenge before the finale.

13.title: Swan Song
13.plot: In a spectacular finale, the artists create a sorcerer and swan for a special performance of Swan Lake by the Los Angeles Ballet.

14.title: Top 20 Countdown: Judges' Favorites
14.plot: Face Off Judges Glenn Hetrick, Ve Neill, and Neville Page take a look back at the best contestant creations from the past five seasons. In addition to ranking the top twenty make ups, these experts call out some of the funniest, most surprising, and impressively ambitious designs the show has ever seen.

1.title: Sexy Beasts
1.plot: An extreme new season of Face Off starts with a bang as 15 new artists work in teams of two to reinvent one of the most classic fairy tale characters of all time - Beast from Beauty and the Beast.

2.title: Cosmic Conspiracy
2.plot: The 14 remaining artists create out-of-this-world alien creatures suffering from an array of interplanetary ailments.

3.title: Dragon's Breath
3.plot: For their first individual Spotlight Challenge, the 13 remaining artists face the monumental task of creating original dragon makeups.

4.title: Guitar Gods
4.plot: The artists get ready to roll 'n rock as they team together to build an original rock star character who has truly become one with an electric guitar.

5.title: In the Shadows
5.plot: The remaining artists take a walk on the dark side as they're tasked with creating supernatural entities based on mysterious silhouettes.

6.title: Cryptic Creatures
6.plot: The artists arrive at a beautiful yet mysterious swamp and learn that they'll be making some famously fabled creatures unknown to science - Cryptids.

7.title: Open Sesame
7.plot: The artists arrive at the mysterious Magic Castle in Hollywood where they learn they'll create unique wizards characters.

8.title: Ego Trip Abroad
8.plot: The artists embark on a trip of a lifetime to Tokyo where they'll gather inspiration for two extreme challenges inspired by the ancient culture of Japan.

9.title: Mad Science
9.plot: Things take a dark turn as the artists play the part of mad scientist and create human guinea pig makeups inspired by bizarre medical devices.

10.title: What a Dahl
10.plot: The artists delve into the whimsical world of children's author Roald Dahl and must create never before seen characters. Screenwriter, author, and Roald Dahl's daughter Lucy Dahl guest judges.

11.title: Freaks of Nature
11.plot: The six remaining artists head to the prestigious Gnomon School of Visual Effects and learn that they will be working with visual effects artists to create original mutants.

12.title: Industrial Revolution
12.plot: The artists head to Union Station and discover that they'll be heading into the future to create original robots tailored to a specific profession.

13.title: Bloodsuckers
13.plot: Pressure mounts as the four remaining artists create legendary vampires from around the world in order to earn a spot in the finale.

14.title: Cry Wolf
14.plot: In the dramatic conclusion to Face Off's first ever two-part challenge, the four remaining artists compete for their spot in the finale by creating werewolf rivals for the legendary vampires they created in the prior episode.

15.title: Heavenly Bodies
15.plot: After a season-long battle, the final three artists must create two rival aliens that can survive a rigorous dance performance.

1.title: Life and Death
1.plot: Season 7 begins in a a big way. As in, the first challenge is actually and audition.

2.title: American Gangster
2.plot: In their first Spotlight Challenge, the surviving artists team up to create a series of Dick Tracy-style gangster makeups inspired by the nicknames of real-life gangsters.

3.title: Ancient Aliens
3.plot: In their first individual Spotlight Challenge, the 13 remaining artists explore the world's great wonders and the ancient aliens who may have helped build them.

4.title: Twisted Trees
4.plot: After a superhero Foundation Challenge, the artists become one with nature as they create fantastically twisted tree characters.

5.title: Animal Attraction
5.plot: The pressure of another individual challenge weighs on all eleven artists as they each have to mash-up two animals to create a unique new species.

6.title: Wizard of Wonderland
6.plot: The artists team up to re-imagine characters from The Wonderful Wizard of Oz as though they've fallen down the rabbit hole into Alice's Wonderland.

7.title: Judge Match
7.plot: Series judges Ve Neill, Neville Page, and Glenn Hetrick compete against each other for charity with the help of a few Face Off all-stars.

8.title: Killer Instinct
8.plot: In partnership with Universal Studios' Halloween Horror Nights, the artists are tasked with creating a horror villain inspired by original movie posters and their tag lines.

9.title: Serpent Soldiers
9.plot: The artists create snake-inspired super soldiers for one of the world's largest franchises, Hasbro's G.I. Joe.

10.title: Scared Silly
10.plot: The eight surviving artists must transform their worst childhood fears into terrifying evil clowns that will have to withstand the rigors of a nightmarish circus performance.

11.title: Teacher's Pets
11.plot: It's back to high school for the remaining artists as they are tasked with creating fun mythical fantasy characters based on classic high school stereotypes.

12.title: Off with Their Heads
12.plot: The artists are given the demanding challenge of creating both a Greek god and the severed head of a beast that has been slain.

13.title: Beautiful Disaster
13.plot: With the semifinals in sight, the final five artists create beautiful elemental fairies born from disastrous scenarios.

14.title: Creature Carnage
14.plot: The four semifinalists must conquer giant city-crushing monsters in order to make it to the finale.

15.title: One Knight Only
15.plot: The epic season of Life and Death reaches a dramatic conclusion in a finale that takes the artists into the fantastical world of Knights.

1.title: Return of the Champions
1.plot: In the first part of this heart-stopping season premiere, contestants are shocked to find out they'll be coached by three former Face Off Champions. Legendary seven-time Oscar Winning makeup effects artist and Special Guest Judge Rick Baker is also on hand to introduce the artists to their first Spotlight Challenge.

2.title: Monkey Business
2.plot: In the exciting conclusion to the season premiere, the champion-led teams of five discover that in addition to the original two aliens, they will be creating a third character, a primate leader. Seven Time Oscar Winner, Rick Baker returns as Guest Judge.

3.title: Let the Games Begin
3.plot: The stakes are at an all-time high as "Hunger Games" film star Josh Hutcherson joins this week's panel to judge the remaining 14 artists in a deadly predator challenge.

4.title: Royal Flush
4.plot: The thirteen remaining artists must make playing cards come to life in the whimsical style of Tim Burton for their first individual Spotlight Challenge of the competition.

5.title: Sounding Off
5.plot: The artists learn that their next Spotlight Challenge will have them designing creatures based solely on unique sound effects created by two-time Academy Award nominated Sound Designer, Erik Aadahl.

6.title: Troll Bridge
6.plot: The stress of another individual Spotlight Challenge weighs on the remaining eleven artists and their coaches as they create trolls inspired by iconic bridges.

7.title: Queen Bees
7.plot: For this week's Spotlight Challenge, the artists find themselves in the middle of the woods where they're shocked to find out they'll be body-painting nude models.

8.title: Dressed to Kill
8.plot: The nine remaining artists tackle a challenge that takes them into the worlds of both fashion and horror as they create makeups worthy of horror icon, Clive Barker.

9.title: Miss Intergalactic
9.plot: A colorful and unconventional Foundation Challenge is followed by the artists being tasked with creating alien beauty queens for the inaugural Miss Intergalactic Pageant, which is judged with help by special guest Gabriela Isler.

10.title: Super Selfies
10.plot: The seven remaining artists find themselves staring down the most daunting challenge in Face Off history, as they must create and apply superhero makeups to themselves!

11.title: Imaginary Friends
11.plot: The six remaining artists are surprised to learn that they will be working with a group of children in a challenge that involves bringing their imaginary friends to life.

12.title: Deadly Dolls
12.plot: As they strive to make the semifinals, the artists must overcome major obstacles in the lab as they give life to creepy dolls. Special Guest Judge, Don Mancini, creator of Chucky.

13.title: Full Steam Ahead
13.plot: The four remaining artists must re-imagine a Western character as a Steampunk cyborg.

14.title: The Dream Team
14.plot: The three finalists tackle the biggest finale challenge in Face Off history, as each must create a team of four unique characters that could star in an original film franchise.

1.title: Intergalactic Zoo
1.plot: Season 9 begins with a cosmic bang as sixteen new talented artists work in teams of two to construct original alien animals that incorporate two models into one massive creation. This difficult task of fashioning the largest creatures ever seen on Face Off proves to be eye opening and taxing for multiple contestants, and a surprise announcement from the judges keeps everyone on edge.

2.title: Siren Song
2.plot: Sixteen artists embark on their next challenge with an assist from the U.S. Coast Guard as they create beautiful but deadly siren makeups inspired by exotic creatures of the sea.

3.title: Surprise of the Century
3.plot: Face Off celebrates its 100th episode in style as the artists turn real-life engaged couples into whimsically macabre characters for a group wedding.

4.title: Frightful Fiction
4.plot: The artists take on Face Off's first ever Focus Challenge in which they are given just two days to create and apply a clean, detailed face makeup based upon literary mash-ups.

5.title: The Gatekeepers
5.plot: The artists compete for immunity in a Foundation Challenge based upon a classic Rorschach inkblot test. For their Spotlight Challenge, they pair off and use a unique gateway as inspiration for two makeups-- a Gatekeeper and whatever is behind the gate.

6.title: Extraterrestrial Enterprise
6.plot: The artists create retro-style aliens for a Foundation Challenge and are then shocked to learn that for their Spotlight Challenge, they must evolve their character into a modern day version of the same alien species.

7.title: All That Glitters
7.plot: The artists are tasked with taking a male model and turning him into a female character from a classic Shakespearean play.

8.title: The Gauntlet
8.plot: The nine artists' skills are put to the ultimate test in a grueling set of three increasingly difficult challenges called The Gauntlet.

9.title: Judgment Day
9.plot: The artists are tasked with bringing their own twist to the Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse.

10.title: Freak Show
10.plot: The seven remaining artists battle for immunity in a barbaric Foundation Challenge judged by Dallas Buyers Club's Oscar-winning makeup artist Robin Matthews. Then it's off to the circus, as they must dazzle the judges with makeups inspired by the freak show.

11.title: Beyond the Expanse
11.plot: As the artists draw closer to the finale, they find themselves tackling a Focus Challenge inspired by he Expanse. Contestants are asked to reimagine human evolution in a disastrous future-Earth scenario.

12.title: Death Becomes Them
12.plot: The five remaining artists are tasked with making quirky and macabre family member characters. They are quickly rattled when they learn that this is the semifinal and two of them will be going home.

13.title: Movie Magic, Part 1
13.plot: The finalists embark on their journey into the Face Off finale challenge, discovering that they'll be working with a real-life Hollywood director and full production crew to create three stunning short films on location.

14.title: Movie Magic, Part 2
14.plot: In the second part of the Face Off finale, the finalists must finish work on their characters for the short film shoots with acclaimed director and creature designer Patrick Tatopoulos.

1.title: Wanted Dead or Alive
1.plot: An all-new season of Face Off begins with a bang as fourteen talented artists work in teams of two to create alien bounty hunters.

2.title: Child's Play
2.plot: The artists work in teams to create a whimsical makeup based on an oversized toy. Special Guest: Paul Reubens (Pee Wee Herman).

3.title: Lost Languages
3.plot: The remaining 12 artists team up to create a member of a long lost race inspired by unique languages created by professional conlanger, David Peterson. Special Guest: David Peterson (language expert, Game of Thrones).

4.title: Covert Characters
4.plot: The eleven artists face the impossible mission of creating a realistic disguise makeup for their first individual, Focus Challenge. Super Producer Gale Anne Hurd serves as Guest Judge.

5.title: Foreign Bodies
5.plot: The artists work in teams of two to create their own parasitic aliens that burst out of their human hosts.

6.title: Death's Doorstep
6.plot: The artists create whimsical ghost characters based on unique and comical obituaries.

7.title: The Gauntlet II
7.plot: It's the return of the two most intimidating words in the competition: the Gauntlet. The eight remaining artists compete in a series of three challenges, with the winners of the first two challenges getting a night on the town and the bottom look from the final challenge heading home.

8.title: Smoke and Mirrors
8.plot: The artists must transform beautiful, yet evil sorceresses into their hideous true selves in a twisted fantasy challenge.

9.title: Bottled Up
9.plot: After transforming winged models into Valkyries for guest judge Douglas Noe in the Foundation Challenge, the artists create Genie makeups inspired by vessels. Guest judge Bill Corso helps series judges decide who stays and who goes home.

10.title: Keep One Eye Open
10.plot: The remaining 5 artists must create a unique Cyclops character in this Focus Challenge. Actor Douglas Smith joins the panel as a Guest Judge.

11.title: The Art of Warcraft
11.plot: The remaining artists venture into Azeroth, converting races from the World of Warcraft into realistic characters for the big screen. On stage, "Warcraft" film star Robert Kazinsky joins the judging panel.

12.title: Skull Island: Reign of Kong
12.plot: In their last challenge before the finale, each artist selects a species from the "Skull Island: Reign of Kong" Universal Orlando attraction and re-imagines its evolution into an intelligent being.

13.title: Sinister Showdown: Part 1
13.plot: The finalists learn that they will each be creating makeups for films adapted from a horror anthology collected by none other than famed director and producer Jason Blum.

14.title: Sinister Showdown: Part 2
14.plot: In part two of the Face Off finale, the three finalists and their teams work on set to each create short horror films before one of them is crowned the new Face Off champion.

1.title: Abstract Aliens
1.plot: In the season premiere, eight teams of returning All-Star artists create unique alien creatures while incorporating green screen technology for the first time in Face Off history.

2.title: The Devil Is in the Details
2.plot: The epic All-Star season continues as the teams work to create angel and devil characters in the first elimination challenge of the season.

3.title: Monster High
3.plot: The artists arrive at Mattel Headquarters where they learn they will be creating film ready versions of "Monster High" characters in this week's immunity challenge.

4.title: Snow Queens
4.plot: In the second elimination challenge of the season, the All-Star teams work to create beautiful snow queens inspired by a series of unique snowflakes.

5.title: Troubling Transformations
5.plot: The competition takes a monstrous turn as the All-Star teams must create two Jekyll and Hyde inspired makeups in this week's elimination challenge for legendary filmmaker and guest judge John Landis.

6.title: Wasteland Warriors
6.plot: The All-Stars strap in for the ride of their lives as they create dystopian characters inspired by post-apocalyptic vehicles for this week's elimination challenge.

7.title: Puppet Masters
7.plot: The episode begins with the suspenseful conclusion to last week's elimination challenge, and transitions into the latest immunity challenge where the teams create magical marionette characters.

8.title: Odd Couples
8.plot: The five remaining All-Star teams create comedic fantasy duos in their latest elimination challenge.

9.title: Frightening Families
9.plot: The remaining artists form two super teams to create a family of deranged, murderous mutants.

10.title: Cursed Covens
10.plot: The two teams must create a coven of warlocks or witches at war with each other.

11.title: Intergalactic Congress
11.plot: The remaining artists, competing individually, must create an alien delegate for an intergalactic congress.

12.title: Tiki Twist
12.plot: The final five must create a representation of a Hawaiian god or goddess.

13.title: Gargoyle Guardians
13.plot: It's the semi-finals! The last four must create a gargoyle inspired by a different style of architecture.

14.title: Battle of the Beasts
14.plot: The final three must create animalistic kung-fu masters for an actual fight scene.

1.title: Pack Leaders
1.plot: In a first, the artists are divided into two make-up effects shop. First assignment: design a werewolf pack.

2.title: Hive Mind
2.plot: Inspired by hive-minded insects, the artists must create queen, worker and drone aliens.

3.title: Dream House
3.plot: A twist with the teams, an assignment to create fairy tale characters. Elizabeth Mitchell guest judges.

4.title: Dante's Demons
4.plot: The artists must create a demon that would oversee a specific circle of Dante's version of Hell.

5.title: String Theory
5.plot: The artists must bring the four seasons to life for a dance to be choreographed by Travis Wall.

6.title: Possessed Possessions
6.plot: The artists must create looks for the owners of possessed objects. Cheyenne Jackson guest judges.

7.title: Feral Fungi
7.plot: The six remaining artists create victims of a fungal virus that turns people into zombies.

8.title: Amusing Aliens
8.plot: The legendary Rick Baker guest judges the artists' alien creations, inspired by real recordings from space.

9.title: Journey Into Fear, Part 1
9.plot: The final three must create creatures for a haunted house conceptualized by series judge Glenn Hetrick.

10.title: Journey Into Fear, Part 2
10.plot: Twists abound for the final three's haunted house challenge. Who will be named winner of Face Off Season 12?

-1.title: Naked & Painted
-1.plot: McKenzie Westmore takes a look at the world of body painting with a variety special guest experts, including the stars of Syfy's upcoming series 'Naked Vegas', former Face Off contestants and the industry's top body painting artists. The special will feature two start-to-finish body painting demonstrations in the lab.

imdb.plot outline: Face Off is a competition/elimination series exploring the world of special-effects make-up artists and the unlimited imagination which allows them to create amazing works of living art. Not only will the show incorporate effects make-up, it will include a wide range of skill sets including prosthetics, 3-D design, animatronics, sculpting, eye enhancers, puppeteering, casting and molding. Each episode involves reveals of the competitors' finished work, and it all culminates in one winner and one grand prize that will launch a career.
imdb.title: Face Off
plot: _Face Off_ (qv) is a competition/elimination series exploring the world of special-effects make-up artists and the unlimited imagination which allows them to create amazing works of living art. Not only will the show incorporate effects make-up, it will include a wide range of skill sets including prosthetics, 3-D design, animatronics, sculpting, eye enhancers, puppeteering, casting and molding. Each episode involves reveals of the competitors' finished work, and it all culminates in one winner and one grand prize that will launch a career.::Anonymous
